(XML Line 000221): Hanging paragraph in clause
	<clause id="_specifications" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><title>Specifications</title><clause id="_general_organoleptic_and_health_characteristics" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><title>General, organoleptic and health characteristics</title><p id="_64e53c18-eb2e-4f7b-b96a-c27c7b8a148d">Kernels of rice, whether parboiled, husked or milled, and whether whole or broken, shall be sound, clean and free from foreign odours or odour which indicates deterioration.</p>
	<p id="_704a7bd4-878f-47f5-9589-fd7839bf35d0">The levels of additives and pesticide residues and other contaminants shall not exceed the maximum limits permitted in the country of destination.</p>
	<p id="_2abebee4-a132-4d49-8705-dcb85e3294f7">The presence of living insects which are visible to the naked eye is not permitted. This should be determined before separating the bulk sample into test samples.</p></clause>
	<clause id="_physical_and_chemical_characteristics" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><title>Physical and chemical characteristics</title><clause id="_846ba5c3-2e2c-4791-bbac-7c6a3d816e9c" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><p id="_c7695a75-014e-4cf6-9db7-1c2cb4e3ee71">The mass fraction of moisture, determined in accordance with <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ISO712" citeas="ISO 712"/>, using an oven complying with the requirements of <eref type="inline" bibitemid="IEC61010-2" citeas="IEC 61010-2"/>, shall not be greater than 15 %.<fn reference="1"><p id="_943f9830-dd12-4b44-b62f-1209deb82185">Formerly denoted as 15 % (m/m).</p></fn></p>
	<p id="_e5221ece-98ff-49bf-bbda-7987d9e34009">The mass fraction of extraneous matter and defective kernels in husked and milled rice, whether or not parboiled, determined in accordance with <xref target="AnnexA"/>, shall not be greater than the values specified in <xref target="table1"/>.</p>
(XML Line 000224): Hanging paragraph in clause
	<clause id="_physical_and_chemical_characteristics" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><title>Physical and chemical characteristics</title><clause id="_846ba5c3-2e2c-4791-bbac-7c6a3d816e9c" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><p id="_c7695a75-014e-4cf6-9db7-1c2cb4e3ee71">The mass fraction of moisture, determined in accordance with <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ISO712" citeas="ISO 712"/>, using an oven complying with the requirements of <eref type="inline" bibitemid="IEC61010-2" citeas="IEC 61010-2"/>, shall not be greater than 15 %.<fn reference="1"><p id="_943f9830-dd12-4b44-b62f-1209deb82185">Formerly denoted as 15 % (m/m).</p></fn></p>
	<p id="_e5221ece-98ff-49bf-bbda-7987d9e34009">The mass fraction of extraneous matter and defective kernels in husked and milled rice, whether or not parboiled, determined in accordance with <xref target="AnnexA"/>, shall not be greater than the values specified in <xref target="table1"/>.</p>
	<note id="_32ee1dae-4354-42af-9465-95c652d9bd46">
	<p id="_9227aff5-b511-49d0-a4d9-c1a3a5860658">Lower mass fractions of moisture are sometimes needed for certain destinations depending on the climate, duration of transport and storage. For further details, see <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ISO6322-1" citeas="ISO 6322-1"/>, <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ISO6322-2" citeas="ISO 6322-2"/> and <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ISO6322-3" citeas="ISO 6322-3"/>.</p>
	</note></clause>
