	<clause id="AnnexA-4-1" inline-header="false" obligation="normative"><title>Preparation of test sample</title><p id="_8328748c-b0e0-43c3-b44e-21d69fc117cb">Carefully mix the laboratory sample to make it as uniform as possible, then proceed to reduce it, using a divider (<xref target="AnnexA-2-1"/>), until a quantity of about 30 g is obtained.</p>
	<p id="_ad2a1dc6-8b8b-408d-bd26-dca937be9531">All parts of kernels which get stuck in the perforations of a sieve should be considered to be retained by the sieve.</p>
	<figure id="figureA-1">
